<article id="post-5437" class="post-5437 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-ccmusic category-reviews tag-ambient tag-jazz tag-love tag-melodic tag-piano tag-thomas-merton has-post-thumbnail">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://cerebralrift.org/2014/07/22/warmth-through-the-broken-lights/" title="Permalink to Warmth Through The Broken Lights" rel="bookmark">Warmth Through The Broken Lights</a></h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-summary">
				<div class="featured-image">
			<a href="http://cerebralrift.org/2014/07/22/warmth-through-the-broken-lights/" title="Warmth Through The Broken Lights">
				<img width="280" height="280" src="http://cerebralrift.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Gustavo_Caldas__Broken_Lights-280x280.jpg" class="attachment-half-width wp-post-image" alt="Warmth Through The Broken Lights" />			</a>
		</div>
		
		<p>I love all sorts of Jazz music, and Gustavo Caldas brings us the warmth through the broken lights in his ambient piano jazz mixed with a bit of mysticism.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-summary -->
	
	<footer class="entry-meta">
